    <main>
      <h2>Crushed Glass</h2>
      <p>Crushed glass rips through my skin;<br>
	A million glistening diamonds<br>
	Sparkling brightly
      </p>

      <p>Like the plain of broken dreams<br>
	Spread over piss stained pavers<br>
	That shine
      </p>

      <p>In the shadow of the clear faced<br>
	Behind the glass there lies<br>
	Nothing
      </p>

      <p>Empty eyes and empty bottles<br>
	Wait in dark corners<br>
	Lost to the world.
      </p>

      <p>Life spills from my veins<br>
	Into the gutters of the streets<br>
	And mixes
      </p>

      <p>With the mud, and shit, and cum<br>
	On Macca's wrappers stomped underfoot<br>
	With brown work boots
      </p>

      <p>The filthy spurts of life<br>
	Slowly congeal;<br>
	In infected waters
      </p>

      <p>Nothing but violence grows.</p>

      <p>Heavy breathing and hostile screams<br>
	Silenced by the glass,<br>
	The invisible screens
      </p>

      <p>The barrier is here<br>
	I feel my heart pounding<br>
	At the rail
      </p>

      <p>Warmth finally<br>
	In this cold metal world
      </p>

      <p>Why don't I jump<br>
	Why don't I jump
      </p>
      
